When MCAs accuse governors of mismanaging funds, being corrupt and inept, it’s just a case of the pot calling the kettle black. Since the Constitution was promulgated in 2010 and devolution came into force, county government leadership has witnessed many challenges, key among them the election of governors and their impeachment.
Granted, devolution is a relatively new concept and leaders may not measure up to the tasks bestowed upon them, but what we have witnessed in some counties is nothing short of infamy. However, it’s common knowledge that governors and ward reps have a love/hate relationship.



